name: The Apache Gold feathers
description:
Native warriors were awarded a feather when they were brave in battle. When a feather falls to earth, the Native Americans believe it carries the energy of its former host to a living being. Feathers are considered gifts from the sky,

Bracelet was hand created and is composed of tiger-eye, died jasper beads, rhinestones and gold filled accents.

name: The Devine Balance Bracelet
description:
The cross is a symbol that needs no explanation. It represents the sacrifice of Christ that was made on Calvary more than 2000 years ago. The beautiful red colored beads represent the blood of his sacrifice.

Piece composed of dyed jasper beads, genuine tiger-eye beads, gold filled accents and rhinestone.

name: Red Dress campaign
description:
National Wear Red Day is the first Friday of February, but why not wear a reminder year round to make others aware of the struggle for great cardiac care for women. 50% of this purchase will go to the Red Dress campaign!!

National Wear Red Day reminds women and those who love them to take action against heart disease. It urges women to eat healthier, be more physically active, and talk to their doctors about their personal risk for heart disease. 

Bracelet made of dyed Jasper beads and red crystal and pewter.

name: The Square Paradigm Bracelet
description: This very stylish bracelet is blinged out and ready to wear. Each time you look at this square remember to never allow anyone or anything to keep you in a box. "Think outside the box."

name: Think Pink
description:
After losing one of the most special women in our lives, Lucille Johnson, we decided to design a bracelet in honor of her and to remind all women and some men to please remember to get regular mammograms. A percentage of the sale of these bracelets will go to support Breast Cancer Research.

Created using pink dyed jasper beads and pewter accents!!

name: Non-Violence
description: This Bracelet is a reminder that every hour of everyday, someone is being victimized by gun violence. We all need to do our part in reducing the impact of violence in America. Our children need to feel safe.

name: Meditation
description: Meditation involves an internal effort to self-regulate the mind in some way. Doing this allows you to elevate your consciousness. Let this awesome bracelet remind you to stop and meditate each day. Pewter charms and turquoise dyed jasper beads and lava accents.

name: Mind and Body
description: Lava rock is in the internal circle of the medicine wheel,  linked with the fire. Lava flows in molten form from a volcano and makes its way above the earth's surface, until it cools and solidifies. Some believe that the rock represents being freed from emotional and physical ruins......Lava accents, pewter, and dyed jasper beads.

name: Creativity
description:
This triangle is a one dimensional representation of a pyramid which is a symbol of life that has perplexed and energized much debate throughout the centuries. There are two dimensions in each of us. There’s the real inner self and the divine self  and then there’s the body and intellect, but at some point we must realize that we are not body, but we exist as a part of a greater consciousness. Find the connection and find your peace. In your peace lies your creativity.
Turquoise dyed jasper beads and pewter charm .

name: Lucky Coin
description: No mystery here. Everybody loves money and think we can all agree that if you have it, you're pretty lucky!! Pewter charm and dyed jasper. Fun to wear!
